text.section:
For the purposes of this section, the failures in the formal requisites of an instrument are:
A defective acknowledgment;
A failure to attach any clerk's certificate;
An omission of a notary seal or other seal;
A lack of or improper acknowledgment or affidavit of consideration, agency, or disbursement;
An omission of an attestation; or
A failure to name any trustee in a deed of trust.
